## Rule: Use `--ld-semantic-color-separator` for All Divider Lines

**Enforcement level: CRITICAL — NO EXCEPTIONS**

---

### When This Rule Applies

Use the separator token any time you need a:

- Horizontal or vertical divider line between sections
- Table row border (`border-bottom` on `<tr>` or `<td>`)
- Card outline where the card acts as a container (not an interactive element)
- Section separator inside a panel, drawer, or page
- Subtle border on a preview frame or documentation card

---

### The Tokens

| Use case | Token | Resolved value |
|---|---|---|
| **Dividers, separators, table rows** | `--ld-semantic-color-separator` | gray-20 `#e3e4e5` — light, true separator |
| **Interactive component borders** (inputs, interactive cards) | `--ld-semantic-color-border-strong` | medium-contrast border |
| **Field borders** | `--ld-semantic-color-field-border` | field-specific border |

---

### Quick Check

```css
/* ❌ WRONG — border-subtle resolves to gray-130 (#515357), near-black — too dark for dividers */
border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ld-semantic-color-border-subtle, #515357);
border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ld-semantic-color-border-subtle, #e6e6e8);
border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ld-semantic-color-border-subtle, #F1F1F2);

/* ✅ CORRECT — separator resolves to gray-20 (#e3e4e5) — correct light divider */
border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ld-semantic-color-separator, #e3e4e5);
```

```tsx
/* ❌ WRONG — hardcoded light gray that bypasses theming */
<div style={{ borderBottom: '1px solid #e6e6e8' }} />

/* ✅ CORRECT */
<div style={{ borderBottom: '1px solid var(--ld-semantic-color-separator, #e3e4e5)' }} />
```

```css
/* ❌ WRONG — for a section divider bar */
.divider {
  background: var(--ld-semantic-color-border-subtle, #e6e6e8);
}

/* ✅ CORRECT */
.divider {
  background: var(--ld-semantic-color-separator, #e3e4e5);
}
```

---

### When to Use `border-subtle` (it still has a purpose)

`--ld-semantic-color-border-subtle` is reserved for **interactive component borders** where a clearly visible, medium-contrast border is appropriate — **not** for dividers:

- Input/text field borders (prefer `--ld-semantic-color-field-border`)
- Dropdown container outlines
- A card that a user can click or hover (interactive card frame)
- Dividers **inside** a component where the design spec explicitly calls for border-subtle

---

### Why This Matters

`--ld-semantic-color-border-subtle` has inconsistent fallback values in the codebase (some use `#515357` which is near-black, others use `#e6e6e8` which is light gray). This inconsistency causes visual bugs — the divider may render too dark in some themes.

`--ld-semantic-color-separator` always resolves to gray-20 (`#e3e4e5`) — a light, unambiguous separator color that works across all themes.

